Package com.taco.suit_lady.view.ui.jfx.lists.treehandler

Class TreeLoader<E extends TreeCellData<T>,​T,​C extends CellController<E>>

java.lang.Object
com.taco.suit_lady.view.ui.jfx.lists.treehandler.TreeLoader<E,​T,​C>
Type Parameters:
E - The type of TreeCellData objects contained within the TreeView managed by this TreeLoader.
T - The type of elements wrapped by the TreeCellData objects contained within the TreeView managed by this TreeLoader.
C - The type of CellController used for each TreeCell of the TreeView managed by this TreeLoader.

    • getObjs

      @NotNull public @NotNull ArrayList<T> getObjs​(@Nullable @Nullable Predicate<T> filter, @Nullable @Nullable javafx.scene.control.TreeItem<E> treeItem, @Nullable @Nullable ArrayList<T> list, int maxSize, @Nullable @Nullable Object... wrappedObjConstructorParams)

      Returns all Wrapped Values in the TreeView loaded by this TreeLoader -- starting with the specified TreeItem as the iteration root -- that match the specified filter.

      Details

      1. Each tested Wrapped Value is retrieved by TreeCellData.createWrappedInstance(Object...).
      2. Only the children of the specified TreeItem -- as well as the item itself -- are tested.
      3. If wrappedObjConstructorParams is null, an empty array is used instead.
      4. If the specified filter is null, wrappedInstance -> true is used instead.
      5. If the specified item is null, this method does nothing and silently returns null.
      6. As soon as the ArrayList is greater than or equal to the specified maxSize, this method returns the list.
        • This means if the specified ArrayList is already larger than the specified maxSize, this method returns immediately.
      7. If the specified maxSize is -1, the size limit is ignored.
      Parameters:
      filter - The filter used to filter through the items in this TreeLoader.
      treeItem - The TreeItem to be used as the starting point of the iteration.
      list - The ArrayList the filtered Values are added to.
      maxSize - The maximum size of the returned ArrayList
      wrappedObjConstructorParams - Passed to the TreeCellData.createWrappedInstance(Object...) as the optional parameters to use upon item construction.
      Returns:
      The specified ArrayList with all Wrapped Values in the TreeView loaded by this TreeLoader that match the specified filter added to it.

    • getValidator

      public final Validatable<T> getValidator()

      Returns the validator used to ensure all items added to the TreeView that is loaded by this TreeLoader adhere to the conditions set by the validator.

      Details

      1. The validator is automatically called when a new item is added to the TreeView that is loaded by this TreeLoader.
      2. The primary usage of the validator is located in the revalidate(TreeItemFX) method.
      Returns:
      The validator used to ensure all items added to the TreeView that is loaded by this TreeLoader adhere to the conditions set by the validator.
